# AW Analysis — Cursor rules

## Project
Cross-asset market intelligence agent. Python 3.11+, src/ layout, package name `aw_analysis`.

## Code style
- British English in comments and docstrings.
- Type hints required on public functions.
- `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of every module.
- Imports: stdlib, third-party, local — separated by blank lines.

## Architecture
- `client/` wraps the Anthropic SDK. Agent code never imports `anthropic` directly.
- `data_sources/` are plain HTTP clients. They know nothing about the agent.
- `tools/` wrap data sources with Anthropic-facing schemas and descriptions.
- `agent/` orchestrates the message loop and tool dispatch.
- `prompts/` hold system prompts as Python constants.

## When editing
- Tool descriptions are load-bearing. Be specific about when to use a tool.
- Errors inside tools should be returned as strings, not raised, so the agent loop survives.
- New tools get registered in `cli/main.py`'s `_build_registry`.

## Stage 5 conventions:
- Every model call goes through AnthropicClient.create with an explicit
  ModelConfig. Never pass model/temperature/max_tokens as bare kwargs.
- Use TaskType enum values, not magic strings.
- Token counts come from client.count_tokens(), never from len(text)/4.
- New per-task settings go in MODEL_CONFIG_REGISTRY in
  aw_analysis/config/model_config.py with a populated rationale field.